h comedy known as the comedia sexy celtibérica), and film directors (Jesús Franco), Pavlović reveals the construction of Spanish national identity through years of cultural tensions.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aArtsxPolitical aspectszSpain. 0aArts, Spanishy20th century. 0aFascism and culturezSpain. 0aGender identity in art. 0aHuman bodyxSymbolic aspectszSpainxHistoryy20th century. 0aPopular culturezSpainxHistoryy20th century. 4aCultural Studies : Cultural Studies. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / Direction & Production.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780791487693423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780791487693/original  a978-3-11-148737-3  SUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles